<tt>slacker</tt> invocation
<p>
<tt>slacker [&lt;OPTIONS&gt;] [&lt;path-filename&gt;]</tt>

Where <bf>OPTIONS</bf> may include any of:
<descrip>
<tag>--doc VALUE</tag>
  where VALUE is one of:
<descrip>
<tag>version</tag>  display version and exit
<tag>help</tag>  display options and exit
<tag>man</tag>  display man and exit
<tag>sgml</tag>  generate SGML invokation info
</descrip>
<tag>--mode VALUE</tag>
  where VALUE is one of:
<descrip>
<tag>capacity</tag>  measure slack capacity of path
<tag>fill</tag>  fill slack space with user data
<tag>frob</tag>  fill slack space with random data
<tag>pour</tag>  write out the contents of slack space
<tag>wipe</tag>  clear the contents of slack space
</descrip>
<tag>--outfile &lt;filename&gt;</tag> write output to ...
<tag>--verbose</tag>	be verbose
<tag>--log-thresh &lt;none | fatal | error | info | branch | progress | entryexit&gt;</tag> logging threshold ...
<tag>--path &lt;filename&gt;</tag> operate on ...
<tag>--recursive</tag>	descend into subdirectories
</descrip>
